<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}-{y}=-{7}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{4}{y}=-{62}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({5},-{8}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --6. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{6}}{{-{{3}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{6}}}{{-{{3}}}}{\left(-{3}{x}+-{1}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{6}}}{{-{{3}}}}{\left(-{7}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{6}\right)}{x}+{2}{y}={14}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{4}{y}=-{62}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{y}=-{48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{48}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}+-{1}{\left(-{8}\right)}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}+{\left({8}\right)}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}=-{7}-{\left({8}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}=-{15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{15}}{{-{{3}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={5}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({5},-{8}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

